 thought of could possibly be called “Life Shield”.  It would take an amount of the caster’s Hit Points and use them as a Rune on a target.  A Druid (or Necromancer, who this spell could also apply to) could cast this on an Enchanter.  The Druid/Necromancer would lose 1,500 Hp and a 1,500 damage absorbing Rune would protect the Enchanter.  This spell should probably have a long recast time, such as 6 to 10 minutes, to prevent its over use.  Also, the caster of the spell should not be able to receive any heals while the spell is still active.  This spell could have a short cast time so that it can be used to save another group member who is under attack and can’t take the hits, such as an enchanter.  It would protect the character while giving time for someone to heal them.<br><br>The next two spells I thought of kind of go together.  They would compliment each other when used together.  One could be called “Form of the Fiery Tiger”.  It would give the illusion of a Tiger, and either an innate 20% to 30% haste or a proc of the same haste.  It could also have a proc of a small fire based DD.  The compliment of this spell would be “Form of the Frozen Croc”.  It would give the illusion of a crocodile and a proc of a Cold Based Slow and DD.  The slow could probably be the same percentage as the haste given to the Tiger spell.  These spells would be like the Enchanter spells “Boon of Garou” and “Trixter’s Augmentation”.  They could have similar mana costs and duration.  <br><br>Another one that I thought of would be one that decreases an opponents ATK rating by a certain percentage.  This spell would decrease the amount of damage done to players.  I don't think it should stack with Slow though, since a mob that is Slowed 75% and then had their attack rating reduced by say 50% would be easily overpowered.  This spell could possibly be part of a cold-based counterpart to the Ro line of Druid spells.<br><br>I don't know how any of these spells would work out in either high end groups or raids, since I've never actually been in any.  Like I said before, these are just spells that I've thought of from time to time.  Maybe one of these would give someone an idea for a spell that would be useful.  *shrugs*<br><br>Heh, thanks for reading my ramblings.  ^_^<br><br>Terfiron Treebreeze<br>Lvl 52 Druid<br>Lanys T'Vyl <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showPrevMessage?topicID=35.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showNextMessage?topicID=35.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://dev.thedruidsgrove.org/images/forum/addreplya.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.emailToFriend?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.threadControl?topicID=35.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=35.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=35.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b